snippet.description:
Presenting "Jumla," a soulful tune with a love story at its core. The words for this song were written by Aman Neelsagar and me. I composed the song, produced it, and performed it. Many aspects of Karnali Province and far-western culture, including the Khas dialect, can be found in this song. This swoon-worthy tune features Miss Pabi and Roshan KC. This music video was filmed across Jumla in several stunning settings. The music video is directed by Shishir Khati.

"Promote Internal Tourism"

snippet.title: Sushant KC - Hawa Le
snippet.description:
I finished my show in the UK, boarded a plane, and got off in Doha. Just as I was ready to head home, I tested positive for covid and what should have been a few hours of transit ended up being a ten-day quarantine. In the boredom of isolation I opened logic on my laptop and what I ended up with was the beat to this song. I got back to Nepal and I scribbled and scribbled till I came up with the lyrics. Then I hit up my friend Nayan and asked him to tag along for a trip to Pokhara. We didn‚Äôt take any heavy equipment with us. Nor did we take a schedule. Yet these random events and decisions gave birth to this gem of a video in such a short time. Thanks to @stellarstudios.np, the most dedicated and awesome team of creators. And thanks to everyone, and every organization involved in this project. Hawa le is a vibe.

snippet.title: How LEECH sucks Blood? #shorts
snippet.description:
#shorts

For "HUGE" Discount on 3D Animation Course, Call: +91-99830-83303 or Click here üëâüèª https://professorofhow.com

How do LEECH suck Blood? #shorts 

Ayurveda has explained Leech therapy, where a leech sucks your blood to cure infections. But are you aware of how a leech actually sucks your blood? Double-tap the screen to understand the process.
A leech uses its head and the sucker present on its tail to stick to a host. After sticking to the host, i.e., you, it releases an anesthetic liquid on your skin, which numbs your skin. Now it uses the 3 sharp jaws present on its head to bite you and you don't feel that bite.
After inserting its jaws into the upper layer of your skin, the leech releases a protein liquid(Hirudin) from its saliva glands. This protein prevents blood clotting in your blood, and because of this, it becomes really easy for the leech to suck your blood using rhythmic movements of its body muscles and store it in its digestive tract. After consuming around 5-15ml of your blood, the leech leaves your skin. Now, this leech could survive for 6 to 9 months with this much blood.
